The Security Council has unanimously stepped up sanctions on North Korea since 2006, with the aim of blunting Pyongyang's funding channels for ballistic and nuclear missile production.
Pompeo met with North Korea's Ri on the sidelines of the U.N. General Assembly. He also announced he would visit Pyongyang again next month for preparations for another summit.
