The group also said the British government was urged to take action to improve maternal and child nutrition through more than 5,000 actions. The government has announced funding for the Power on Nutrition project, which focuses on tackling malnutrition and reaches 5 million mothers and children.
One of the questions in the Frequently Asked Questions column on the movement's website reads: "why do you think we can bring an end to extreme poverty?"
The Global citizen's response: "The road will be long and difficult and many stumbling blocks lie ahead of us.
But we will succeed, like the great civil rights struggles and anti-apartheid movements before us, because together we will be stronger."
